==== ENTRY 9 ====
HEADWORD: Hack
<hw>Hack</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To use as a hack; to
let out for hire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To use frequently and indiscriminately, so as to
render trite and commonplace.</def><-- = hackney? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The word ⟦ldquo⟧remarkable⟦rdquo⟧ has been so <qex>hacked</qex> of
late.</q> <rj><qau>J. H. Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hack</ent>⟦br⟧

